object.Almond.name: Almond
object.Almond.description: A drupe consisting of an outer hull and a hard shell with the seed within.
object.Asian Pear.name: Asian Pear
object.Asian Pear.description: Not to be confused with the normal pear.
object.Avocado.name: Avocado
object.Avocado.description: A soft plant that is a popular topping and addition to many meals. It is particularly loved by younger generations.
object.Breadfruit.name: Breadfruit
object.Breadfruit.description: A relative of the jackfruit. It has a robust flavor that is surprisingly fruity and sweet.
object.Camphor Leaves.name: Camphor Leaves
object.Camphor Leaves.description: Glossy oval leaves that are very fragrant when crushed.
object.Cashew.name: Cashew
object.Cashew.description: A buttery nut that buds at the bottom of the cashew apple.
object.Cinnamon Sticks.name: Cinnamon Sticks
object.Cinnamon Sticks.description: Its scent is uniquely warming, uplifting, and stimulating, and its flavor sweet and delicious.
object.Cocoa Pod.name: Cocoa Pod
object.Cocoa Pod.description: The pod obtained from a cocoa tree. Mmm! Who's ready to make some chocolate?
object.Dragon Fruit.name: Dragon Fruit
object.Dragon Fruit.description: Also called a pitaya, this is the fruit of a large cactus.
object.Durian.name: Durian
object.Durian.description: A smelly fruit with a spiky husk.
object.Eucalyptus Leaves.name: Eucalyptus Leaves
object.Eucalyptus Leaves.description: Leathery blue-green leaves are studded with glands containing a fragrant, volatile oil. Luckily not an exploding oil!
object.Fig.name: Fig
object.Fig.description: A small and sweet fruit. It is soft and delicious.
object.Fragrant Wisteria.name: Fragrant Wisteria
object.Fragrant Wisteria.description: An especially fragrant cluster of purple flowers.
object.Granny Smith Apple.name: Granny Smith Apple
object.Granny Smith Apple.description: The flavor is tart and acidic, but it makes for a good baking apple.
object.Grapefruit.name: Grapefruit
object.Grapefruit.description: A large bitter fruit, high in Vitamin C. Are you a salty or sugary kind of person?
object.Lemon.name: Lemon
object.Lemon.description: A tangy citrus fruit that is used to make lemonade.
object.Lime.name: Lime
object.Lime.description: The tarter cousin of the lemon. It is often used as an accent to numerous dishes.
object.Lychee.name: Lychee
object.Lychee.description: The outside is roughly textured and inedible, but the inside is sweet.
object.Melaleuca Leaves.name: Melaleuca Leaves
object.Melaleuca Leaves.description: A prickly cone of leaves that are often used as a homemade remedy for cuts and bruises.
object.Olive.name: Olive
object.Olive.description: It is packed with vitamins! Olives are used to make oil and salads.
object.Papaya.name: Papaya
object.Papaya.description: A tropical fruit from the rainforest. It has a sweet flavor and a lot of natural juiciness.
object.Pear.name: Pear
object.Pear.description: A mildly sweet fruit that grows in the winter. Let it ripen for a few days before eating.
object.Pecan.name: Pecan
object.Pecan.description: A savory nut with a striped seed. Do you own a nutcracker?
object.Persimmon.name: Persimmon
object.Persimmon.description: A somewhat uncommon fruit filled with a honey-like flavor.
object.Pomelo.name: Pomelo
object.Pomelo.description: A really large, not so bitter, cousin of the grapefruit.
object.Ume.name: Ume
object.Ume.description: A sweet and sour green fruit. It used to preserved with sugar or salt.
object.Vanilla.name: Vanilla
object.Vanilla.description: Easily be one of the most well-known flavors in the world. Who's hungry for ice cream?
object.Walnut.name: Walnut
object.Walnut.description: A nut that makes delicious candies and pies. It is often used in the filling of sweet treats.
object.Ylang Ylang.name: Ylang Ylang
object.Ylang Ylang.description: A highly appreciated flower in perfumery and aromatherapy.
object.Yuzu.name: Yuzu
object.Yuzu.description: A aromatic citrus fruit that is used to preserved with sugar.
